cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CV 

This paper is about extending recurrent neural networks (RNNs) to deep RNNs, which is a topic that falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed deep RNNs on tasks related to natural language processing (language modeling) and computer vision (polyphonic music prediction), which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel framework based on neural operators, which could place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents empirical results that support the proposed approach, which could make it relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
